<Link id="l01199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1199"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1200"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Splits block B into a sequence of smaller blocks.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1201"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1202"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// SplitOffsets should be a sequence of ascending offsets in B. The starting</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1203"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// offset should be greater than zero, and the final offset less than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1204"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// B.getSize() - 1</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1205"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1206"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The resulting seqeunce of blocks will start with the original block B</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1207"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// (truncated to end at the first split offset) followed by newly introduced</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1208"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// blocks starting at the subsequent split points.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1209"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1210"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The optional Cache parameter can be used to speed up repeated calls to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1211"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// splitBlock for blocks within a single Section. If the value is None then</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1212"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the cache will be treated as uninitialized and splitBlock will populate</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1213"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// it. Otherwise it is assumed to contain the list of Symbols pointing at B,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1214"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// sorted in descending order of offset.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1215"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1216"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1217"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Notes:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1218"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1219"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 1 splitBlock must be used with care. Splitting a block may cause</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1220"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    incoming edges to become invalid if the edge target subexpression</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1221"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    points outside the bounds of the newly split target block (E.g. an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1222"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    edge &#39;S + 10 : Pointer64&#39; where S points to a newly split block</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1223"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    whose size is less than 10). No attempt is made to detect invalidation</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1224"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    of incoming edges, as in general this requires context that the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1225"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    LinkGraph does not have. Clients are responsible for ensuring that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1226"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    splitBlock is not used in a way that invalidates edges.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1227"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1228"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 2 The newly introduced blocks will have new ordinals that will be higher</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1229"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    than any other ordinals in the section. Clients are responsible for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1230"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    re-assigning block ordinals to restore a compatible order if needed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1231"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1232"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 3 The cache is not automatically updated if new symbols are introduced</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1233"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    between calls to splitBlock. Any newly introduced symbols may be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1234"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    added to the cache manually (descending offset order must be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1235"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    preserved), or the cache can be set to None and rebuilt by</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01236" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1236"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    splitBlock on the next call.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1237"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> SplitOffsetRange&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01238" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1238" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/linkgraph/#a9fe06e224ae04245f0c9f61365aafde4"><Highlight kind="normal">  std::vector&lt;Block &#42;&gt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/linkgraph/#a9fe06e224ae04245f0c9f61365aafde4">splitBlock</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/block">Block</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>, SplitOffsetRange &amp;&amp;SplitOffsets,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1239"><Highlight kind="normal">                                  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/linkgraph/#afc87be5343187a4cef74ac1a22d4a2b2">LinkGraph::SplitBlockCache</a> &#42;Cache = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">nullptr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1240"><Highlight kind="normal">    std::vector&lt;Block &#42;&gt; Blocks;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1242"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1243"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (std::empty(SplitOffsets))</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1245"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
